'''Christopher Bonsu Baah''' (born 14 December 2004) is a Ghanaian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] side [[Al Qadsiah FC|Al-Qadsiah]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Club career==
===Sarpsborg===
Bonsu Baah joined Norwegian [[Eliteserien]] side [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]] from Ghanaian second division side Accra Shooting Stars in March 2023.<ref name=sb>{{cite web|url=https://www.sarpsborg08.no/nyheter/christopher-bonsu-baah-klar-for-sarpsborg-08|title=Christopher Bonsu Baah klar for Sarpsborg 08|trans-title=Christopher Bonsu Baah ready for Sarpsborg 08|date=13 March 2023|accessdate=30 June 2023|website=sarpsborg08.no|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsworldghana.com/ghanaian-teenager-christopher-bonsu-joins-sarpsborg/|title=Ghanaian teenager Christopher Bonsu joins Sarpsborg|first=Edmund|last=Okai Gyimah|date=15 April 2023|accessdate=30 June 2023|website=sportsworldghana.com}}</ref> The Norwegian side stated in their announcement that Bonsu Baah had previously trialed with [[Borussia Dortmund]], [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]], [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref name=sb/>

Bonsu Baah scored his first goal for Sarpsborg in a 3–1 win against [[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]], and his impressive performances for the club earned him a place on the 2023 [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] longlist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kickgh.com/more/ghanaians-abroad/23612-ghanaian-teenager-christopher-bonsu-baah-nets-debut-goal-in-sarpsborg-08-win-over-aalesunds-fk|title=Ghanaian teenager Christopher Bonsu Baah nets debut goal in Sarpsborg 08 win over Aalesunds FK|date=29 May 2023|accessdate=30 June 2023|website=kickgh.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/ghanaian-duo-ernest-nuamah-and-baah-bonsu-nominated-for-golden-boy-award|title=Ghanaian duo Ernest Nuamah and Baah Bonsu nominated for Golden Boy award|date=20 June 2023|accessdate=30 June 2023|website=ghanasoccernet.com}}</ref>

===Genk===
On 6 July 2023, only four months after joining Sarpsborg, Bonsu Baah signed for [[Belgian Pro League]] side [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] on a five-year deal.<ref name=krcg>{{cite web|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/5164/18-jarig-talent-christopher-bonsu-baah-tekent-voor-5-jaar-bij-krc-genk|title=18-jarig talent Christopher Bonsu Baah tekent voor 5 jaar bij KRC Genk|trans-title=18-year-old talent Christopher Bonsu Baah signs for 5 years with KRC Genk|date=6 July 2023|accessdate=6 July 2023|website=krcgenk.be|language=Dutch}}</ref>

===Al-Qadsiah===
On 7 July 2025, Bonsu Baah joined Saudi Arabian side [[Al Qadsiah FC|Al-Qadsiah]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=بونسو باه يعزز القادسية |url=http://arriyadiyah.com/869591}}</ref>

==Style of play==
A left-footed right-winger, also capable of playing as an [[attacking midfielder]], Bonsu Baah led the Norwegian Eliteserien with 57 successful dribbles and 10 chances created, during his time with Sarpsborg.<ref name=krcg/>

==International career==
Bonsu Baah was called up to the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]] for the [[2025 Unity Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanafa.org/otto-addo-names-squad-for-unity-cup-2025|title=Otto Addo names squad for Unity Cup 2025|first=Ghana Football|last=Association|website=www.ghanafa.org}}</ref>
In March 2025, Bonsu Baah received his first senior call-up to the Ghana national team for the 2026 FIFA World Cup qualification matches against Chad and Madagascar.

In June 2026, he was named in Ghana’s final squad for the 2026 FIFA World Cup after an impressive season with Al-Qadsiah. <ref>{{cite web |title=Christopher Bonsu Baah buzzing after earning Ghana World Cup call-up |url=https://footy-africa.com/christopher-bonsu-baah-buzzing-after-earning-ghana-world-cup-call-up/ |website=Footy-Africa |date=2026-06-02 |access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref>

